{
  "topicId": "m7-t1",
  "title": "Talking about Habits and Routines",
  "dialect": "egyptian-arabic",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The Present Tense for Habits"
        },
        "text": "In Egyptian Arabic, we use the present tense to talk about actions that happen regularly, our daily routines, and general habits. This is similar to how \"I do\" or \"I am doing\" works in English, but for habits, it always implies regularity.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا آكل",
            "english": "I eat",
            "transliteration": "Ana ākol"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أذهب",
            "english": "I go",
            "transliteration": "Ana azhab"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أنام",
            "english": "I sleep",
            "transliteration": "Ana anām"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "To Get Up / To Wake Up (أصحى)"
        },
        "text": "The verb \"أصحى\" (asˤḥa) means \"I wake up\" or \"I get up\". This is a common part of anyone's morning routine.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أصحى الساعة سبعة الصبح.",
            "english": "I wake up at 7 AM.",
            "transliteration": "Ana asˤḥa as-sāʿa sabʿa es-ṣubḥ."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "To Eat Breakfast (أفطر)"
        },
        "text": "After waking up, many people \"أفطر\" (afṭar), which means \"I eat breakfast\". The word for breakfast itself is \"فطار\" (fiṭār).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أفطر كل يوم.",
            "english": "I eat breakfast every day.",
            "transliteration": "Ana afṭar kull yōm."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الفطار جاهز.",
            "english": "Breakfast is ready.",
            "transliteration": "El-fiṭār gāhiz."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "أنا أصحى بدري.",
        "english": "I wake up early.",
        "transliteration": "Ana asˤḥa badrī."
      },
      "context": "Common phrase to describe waking up early."
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "أنا أفطر الساعة تسعة.",
        "english": "I eat breakfast at nine o'clock.",
        "transliteration": "Ana afṭar as-sāʿa tisʿa."
      },
      "context": "Stating the time of breakfast."
    },
