    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "To Go (أروح)"
        },
        "text": "The verb \"أروح\" (arūḥ) means \"I go\". It's used for going to places like work, school, or home.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أروح الشغل كل يوم.",
            "english": "I go to work every day.",
            "transliteration": "Ana arūḥ esh-shoġl kull yōm."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أروح المدرسة.",
            "english": "I go to school.",
            "transliteration": "Ana arūḥ el-madrasa."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "To Return / To Come Back (أرجع)"
        },
        "text": "\"أرجع\" (argaʿ) means \"I return\" or \"I come back\". It's often used when coming back from work, school, or an outing.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أرجع البيت متأخر.",
            "english": "I return home late.",
            "transliteration": "Ana argaʿ el-bēt mitʾakhkhar."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أرجع من الشغل الساعة خمسة.",
            "english": "I come back from work at 5 o'clock.",
            "transliteration": "Argaʿ men esh-shoġl as-sāʿa khamsa."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Every Day (كل يوم)"
        },
        "text": "To express that something happens daily, we use the phrase \"كل يوم\" (kull yōm). It's crucial for describing routines.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أروح الشغل كل يوم.",
            "english": "I go to work every day.",
            "transliteration": "Ana arūḥ esh-shoġl kull yōm."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أصحى بدري كل يوم.",
            "english": "I wake up early every day.",
            "transliteration": "Ana asˤḥa badrī kull yōm."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
