    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "To Watch (أتفرج)"
        },
        "text": "The verb \"أتفرج\" (atfarraɡ) means \"I watch\". It's commonly used for watching TV, movies, or sports.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أتفرج على التليفزيون.",
            "english": "I watch TV.",
            "transliteration": "Ana atfarraɡ ʿala at-tilifizyōn."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أتفرج على فيلم كل ليلة.",
            "english": "I watch a movie every night.",
            "transliteration": "Ana atfarraɡ ʿala film kull lēla."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "To Eat Dinner (أتعشى)"
        },
        "text": "\"أتعشى\" (atʿashsha) means \"I eat dinner\". The word for dinner is \"عشا\" (ʿasha).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أتعشى الساعة ثمانية.",
            "english": "I eat dinner at 8 o'clock.",
            "transliteration": "Ana atʿashsha as-sāʿa tamanya."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "العشا جاهز.",
            "english": "Dinner is ready.",
            "transliteration": "El-ʿasha gāhiz."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "To Sleep (أنام)"
        },
        "text": "The verb \"أنام\" (anām) means \"I sleep\". It's the final part of a typical daily routine.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أنام بدري كل يوم.",
            "english": "I sleep early every day.",
            "transliteration": "Ana anām badrī kull yōm."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أنام الساعة عشرة بالليل.",
            "english": "I sleep at 10 PM.",
            "transliteration": "Ana anām as-sāʿa ʿashara bil-lēl."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
