    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "To Read (أقرأ)"
        },
        "text": "The verb \"أقرأ\" (aqraʾ) means \"I read\". It can refer to reading books, newspapers, or anything else.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أقرأ كتاب قبل ما أنام.",
            "english": "I read a book before I sleep.",
            "transliteration": "Ana aqraʾ kitāb qabl ma anām."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا أقرأ الجرنال كل يوم الصبح.",
            "english": "I read the newspaper every morning.",
            "transliteration": "Ana aqraʾ el-gurnāl kull yōm es-ṣubḥ."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "To Exercise / To Play Sports (ألعب رياضة)"
        },
        "text": "To say \"I exercise\" or \"I play sports\", we use \"ألعب رياضة\" (alʿab riyāḍa). \"ألعب\" (alʿab) means \"I play\", and \"رياضة\" (riyāḍa) means \"sport/exercise\".",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا ألعب رياضة مرتين في الأسبوع.",
            "english": "I exercise twice a week.",
            "transliteration": "Ana alʿab riyāḍa marratēn fil-usbūʿ."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا بحب ألعب رياضة.",
            "english": "I like to exercise.",
            "transliteration": "Ana baḥibb alʿab riyāḍa."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
